# Design (Flowboard)

Use this rule when building or styling components so the UI stays consistent. The product aims for a **Linear-like** look: dark-first, minimal, subtle borders, semantic colors for status/priority.

## Design tokens

**Defined in:** `frontend/app/app.css` (CSS variables) and `frontend/app/lib/design-tokens.ts` (task colors).

### Colors (CSS variables)

- **Backgrounds:** `--bg`, `--bg-subtle`, `--surface`, `--surface-hover`
- **Text:** `--text`, `--text-muted`, `--text-subtle`
- **Borders:** `--border`, `--border-muted`, `--border-hover`
- **Actions:** `--accent`, `--accent-hover`
- **Semantic:** `--red`, `--amber`, `--blue`, `--green`, `--purple` (status/priority)
- **Focus:** `--ring`

Use in Tailwind via arbitrary values: `bg-[var(--surface)]`, `text-[var(--text-muted)]`, `border-[var(--border)]`.

### Task colors

Import from `~/lib/design-tokens`:

- `PRIORITY_COLORS` — LOW, MEDIUM, HIGH, URGENT (map to CSS vars)
- `TYPE_COLORS` — TASK, BUG, HOTFIX, FEATURE, IMPROVEMENT, TEST

Use for badges, dots, and inline styles (e.g. `backgroundColor: PRIORITY_COLORS[priority]`).

### Radius

- `--radius: 6px` — inputs, buttons, small controls → use `rounded-md`
- `--radius-card: 8px` — cards can use `rounded-xl` (12px) per existing Card component

## Typography

- **Font:** Poppins (weights 400, 500, 600). Loaded in `root.tsx` via Google Fonts.
- **Body:** 13px, weight 400, line-height 1.5–1.6
- **Headings:** h1 18px, h2 15px, h3–h6 13px; weight 600; `tracking-tight` / `-0.02em` for titles
- **Labels / inputs:** weight 500
- **Section labels:** 10px, uppercase, `tracking-[0.06em]` or `tracking-[0.1em]`, `text-[var(--text-subtle)]`
- **Form labels in modals:** `font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.06em] text-[var(--text-subtle)]`
- **Small / meta:** 11px, 12px with `font-mono` for codes/timestamps

## Spacing

- **Label to input:** `space-y-1.5`
- **Form sections:** `space-y-4`, `gap-4`, `gap-8` for larger blocks
- **Side-by-side fields:** `grid grid-cols-2 gap-3`
- **Dialog content:** `p-6`; footer `gap-2`
- **Nav items:** `px-4 py-1.5`
- **Sheet padding:** `px-6 py-5` (header), `px-6 py-6` (body)

## Component patterns (consistent in this codebase)

- **Inputs:** `rounded-md border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--bg-subtle)] text-[13px] font-light`
- **Select trigger:** `rounded-md border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--surface)]` (or `bg-[var(--bg-subtle)]`)
- **Dropdown / popover content:** `border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--surface)]`
- **Primary button:** `bg-[var(--accent)] text-[var(--primary-foreground)] hover:bg-[var(--accent-hover)]`
- **Outline button:** `border-[var(--border)] text-[var(--text-muted)] hover:bg-[var(--surface-hover)] hover:text-[var(--text)]`
- **Danger:** `text-[var(--red)]` or `hover:text-[var(--red)]`; destructive button `bg-[var(--red)]`
- **Focus ring:** `focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-[var(--ring)]` or `focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[var(--border-hover)]`

## What “consistent” means here

- Prefer **CSS variables** over hardcoded hex/tailwind color names so light/dark and tokens stay in sync.
- Use **design-tokens.ts** for task priority/type colors instead of redefining in components.
- Match **typography**: 13px body, 10px uppercase labels, 18px page titles.
- Use **rounded-md** for form controls and **rounded-xl** for cards.
- Keep **spacing** predictable: `space-y-1.5` for label+input, `gap-3`/`gap-4` for sections.
